# Agent Documentation

This directory contains agent-agnostic reference docs that any AI coding agent (Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Windsurf, Aider) loads on demand.

## Why this structure exists

LLMs reliably follow ~150-200 instructions before degrading. If we put every rule in the root `AGENTS.md`, we'd burn the budget on rules that don't apply to the current task.

Instead, we use **progressive disclosure**:

1. **Root `AGENTS.md`** - always loaded. Universal rules + reference table only. Kept slim. (Claude Code reads this as a fallback when `CLAUDE.md` doesn't exist; Codex / Cursor / Windsurf / Aider read it natively.)
2. **Skills + nested `AGENTS.md`** - auto-activated when relevant. Skills match by description, nested files load when editing their directory.
3. **`docs/ai/` reference docs** (this folder) - the source of truth. Loaded when the root file / skills tell the agent to.

See `writing-docs.md` for the full architecture and rules for editing these files.

